<div id="review_3494650031" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3494650031" />
    <a title="Hilary Parsons" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/74876845-hilary-parsons"><img alt="Hilary Parsons" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1513070021p2/74876845.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3494650031?book_show_action=true">Aug 14, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hilary Parsons" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hilary Parsons" href="/user/show/74876845-hilary-parsons">Hilary Parsons</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3494650031" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer739232834511269395">A great book to read if you’re wanting learn more about economics and finance. Ferguson eloquently covers the histories behind common economic establishments and practises. He grasps the readers interest by showing their current relevance. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


